"From the Publisher: ::: A detailed analysis of technological and legal issues that arise when contracting through electronic means or other electronic data interchanges. Discusses electronics/computer technology, its regulation and various trading partner agreements and third party service provider agreements. Combines the technology with various legal transactions to explain how this form of contracting and communication interacts with traditional legal concerns of contracts, intellectual property, trade secrets, patents and trademarks, service provider liability and antitrust law."
